  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper reports two new rigid multiple-resonance thermally activated delayed fluorescence (MR-TADF) green emitters, tCzphB-Ph and tCzphB-Fl, designed by locking phenyl groups in a BN-core framework with spiro-carbon bridges. The molecules show unusually narrow green emission (down to 14 nm FWHM in cyclohexane, CIE y up to 0.77) and enable high-performance OLEDs, including a BT.2020-compatible green device with high EQE and very high luminance.",
